{"questionId":"9827","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Happy Straw Company manufactures drinking straws.</p>\n<p>The straws are packaged in small closed rectangular boxes, each with length 8 cm, width 4 cm&nbsp;and height 3 cm. The information is shown in the diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2e2c01e0ec88edea5a6fb1b1e3c4e5513ac32546.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the surface area of the box in cm<sup>2</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\">2(8 × 4&nbsp;+ 3 × 4 + 3 × 8)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">= 136 (cm<sup>2</sup>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9827","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.4a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the surface area of the box in cm2.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}